parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to suddenly and rapidly lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine misfires
stumbles
or loses power
especially when accelerating or driving at high speeds. The check engine light may come on
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" with reduced power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks and Spark Plug Fouling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and spark plug fouling can cause the engine to misfire, stumble, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine misfires
stumbles
or loses power
especially when accelerating or driving at high speeds. The check engine light may come on
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" with reduced power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine quit can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine quits or stalls while driving
especially when making turns or decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The cluster lights do not turn on
the speedometer
tachometer
temperature
and fuel gauges do not function
and the dimmer switch does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may go into "limp" mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to come on and may lead to airbag malfunction.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
and the clock spring may cause a poor connection to the main wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the stereo and alarm system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The stereo cuts on and off
and the car alarm goes off randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The starter motor drags every time the vehicle is started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the horn can cause the driver to be unable to alert other drivers or pedestrians, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The horn is very stiff and requires a lot of force to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
surges forward
or continues to accelerate even when the brake pedal is applied
making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not engage or are ineffective
causing the vehicle to continue moving even when the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not stay engaged
is difficult to turn on
or causes unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine throttle sticking can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine throttle sticks
usually when the brakes are applied
causing the vehicle to surge forward or accelerate unexpectedly.
